Ask HN: Is this new ThinkPad E14 worth it to bother with warranty?
text:
So I bought a new ThinkPad E14 Gen2 for 560 euros in the Baltic market. It has 15.2 GB of usable RAM instead of 16GB stated and 930GB SSD instead of 1Tb stated by the vendor mdata.lt. No wonder they were reluctant for me to check the SSD storage upon delivery. Hope that they go bankrupt and hang their useless selves in theirs useless offices.

It also has a backlit keyboard, aluminum casing on top and probably PC + ABS casing on the bottom, AMD 3 4300U 4 core CPU, Windows10 pre-installed, 2 year warranty.

I can buy a refurbished T480 for ~500 euros with the 1Tb SSD and 16GB RAM + 2 year warranty for the Thinkpad and 6 month warranty for the battery from another vendor. Or a new L14 G1 with 8gb RAM, 256 GB SSD, AMD Ryzen 5 6 core and backlit keyboard for ~670 euros (no soldered RAM) from another vendor.

Should I bother to send this E14 for incorrect specs (the discrepancy in which basically may not matter much for me for now)?
